00:54:47.367 --> 00:54:49.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now let’s enjoy our video postcard.

00:54:49.970 --> 00:54:54.507 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This month we visit
our brothers and sisters in Guyana.

00:54:54.507 --> 00:54:58.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This country of more than 750,000 people

00:54:58.511 --> 00:55:01.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is in the northeastern corner
of South America.

00:55:01.781 --> 00:55:05.552 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is a land of lush rain forests,

00:55:05.552 --> 00:55:09.556 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
sugarcane plantations, and open grasslands.

00:55:09.556 --> 00:55:14.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Temperatures and humidity are high,
and the rainfall is heavy.

00:55:14.461 --> 00:55:18.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In fact, Guyana means “land of water.”

00:55:18.698 --> 00:55:21.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These brothers
are with the congregation in Charity,

00:55:21.368 --> 00:55:24.738 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a part of Guyana known
for extensive preaching done along the river.

00:55:25.672 --> 00:55:28.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
More than half
of Guyana’s population is rural,

00:55:28.174 --> 00:55:32.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and most people live in villages
in the coastal region.

00:55:32.412 --> 00:55:35.915 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Baramita,
a Carib-language-speaking community

00:55:35.915 --> 00:55:37.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
known for gold mining.

00:55:37.917 --> 00:55:40.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The congregation’s 119 publishers

00:55:40.687 --> 00:55:45.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
conduct an average
of 228 Bible studies every month.

00:55:46.459 --> 00:55:48.962 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Baramita is also home
to a remote translation office.

00:55:51.464 --> 00:55:54.901 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many people live scattered
throughout the surrounding dense jungle.

00:55:54.901 --> 00:55:58.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And reaching them
requires hours and hours of walking.

00:55:59.606 --> 00:56:02.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because the rainy season
is over half of the year,

00:56:02.409 --> 00:56:04.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
travel can be very difficult.

00:56:04.444 --> 00:56:07.947 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But our brothers and sisters
—they’re not deterred by the terrain.

00:56:08.848 --> 00:56:12.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, these are typical dwellings
of the Carib community in Baramita.

00:56:12.852 --> 00:56:16.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And, our brothers
—they preach to everyone they encounter,

00:56:16.856 --> 00:56:19.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from cassava farmers to gold miners.

00:56:20.760 --> 00:56:23.396 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers and sisters
in the Baramita Congregation

00:56:23.396 --> 00:56:27.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send you their warm love and greetings.

00:56:27.067 --> 00:56:29.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:56:29.335 --> 00:56:31.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

